  "prompt": "How do I ask for a full-time offer from an internship manager?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for asking for a full-time offer:\n\n1. Timing\n- Wait until near the end of your internship\n- Choose a moment when your manager seems receptive\n- Ideally, schedule a formal meeting\n\n2. Preparation\n- Gather evidence of your contributions\n- Document specific projects and achievements\n- Demonstrate how you've added value to the team\n\n3. Conversation approach\n- Be direct but professional\n- Express genuine interest in the company\n- Highlight your passion for the role/team\n- Ask about potential full-time opportunities\n\n4. Sample script\n\"I've really enjoyed my time here and feel I've made meaningful contributions. I'm very interested in continuing to grow with [Company Name]. Are there any full-time opportunities available that might be a good fit?\"\n\n5. Follow-up strategies\n- If no immediate opportunity exists, ask about future possibilities\n- Request feedback on skills you could develop\n- Stay connected with your manager/team\n- Keep networking within the organization\n\n6. Additional tips\n- Maintain a positive, professional attitude\n- Be patient\n- Continue performing excellently\n- Have a backup plan if the offer doesn't materialize\n\nConfidence and preparation are key when approaching this conversation.",
